As the name suggests, Patagonia’s ‘Woolyester’ pullover fleece is made from a mix of premium fabrics including recycled wool and polyester.

Fitted with a protective funnel neckline, this popover ‘Woolyester’ fleece from Californian label Patagonia is – as the name suggests – made from a mix of premium fabrics including recycled wool and polyester.
Trimmed with contrasting navy blue detailing, Californian label Patagonia present their winter-ready ‘Woolyester’ pullover this season.

This cosy, fleece-lined hoody by revered Italian casuals brand Stone Island is garment dyed to create its rich, pitch black colour. It is crafted from pure soft cotton and is finished with chunky drawstrings at the hood and a snug kangaroo-style pocket at the front.

This military green hoody by Stone Island, the favoured football terrace brand, is a sleekly cut athleisure piece, made to exacting standards to ensure longevity. It is crafted from pure cotton, fleece-brushed on the inside, and finished with a snug hood and roomy pouch pocket.

In deep, night-sky blue, this Stone Island sweater is an everyday athleisure piece that packs a high fashion punch. Crafted from pure soft cotton and finished with the brand’s iconic compass patch at the sleeve, it has been designed with cutting edge tailoring expertise for ultimate longevity.

This pure cotton crewneck sweater by Stone Island is garment dyed to a perfect shade of dusky terracotta. Channelling the brand’s commitment to pared-back utilitarian design, it is simply cut and marked with Stone Island’s iconic compass patch at the sleeve.

The rich red wine tone of this pure cotton pullover by Stone Island makes it a great everyday go-to, whatever you’re wearing. Channelling the brand’s commitment to finely crafted athleisurewear, it is cut from pure, soft cotton and garment dyed for a worn-in aesthetic.

Garment-dyed for rich colour and a vintage feel, this soft cotton sweatshirt by Stone Island neatly embodies the expert tailoring and utilitarian styling the brand has always championed. Presented in a deep grey tone, it’s finished with a classic, comfortable crewneck and finished with the label’s iconic compass motif at the sleeve.
This carefully cut cotton sweater by Stone Island is presented in 2019’s favourite colour

A classic piece of Californian skate wear that’s sure to transition from season to season with ease, this Stüssy hoody is crafted in a comfortable cotton blend construction. Branded proudly at its chest, the pullover boasts a practical pouch pocket and it cuffs and hem are completed with cosy ribbed knits.

Promising to brighten up your off-duty rotation, Stüssy present a vibrant take on their signature hoody. Capturing attention with its electric blue outer, this head-turning sweat is lined with an ultra-soft fleece, providing cosy comfort with every wear.

Stepping back in time to achieve a retro aesthetic, Stüssy deliver this black hoody as part of their latest skate-inspired collection. Made from the finest fleeceback jersey, its popover build is branded with a hot pink logo appliqué; while a handy kangaroo pocket leaves a functional finishing touch at the front.

Stepping back in time to achieve a retro aesthetic, Stüssy deliver this grey hoody as part of their latest skate-inspired collection. Made from the finest fleeceback jersey, its popover build is branded with a hot pink logo appliqué; while a handy kangaroo pocket leaves a functional finishing touch at the front.

Saint Laurent is a brand with rich Parisian heritage and for AW19 it becomes self-referential, hopping back in time to the ‘60s to revive this incarnation of its logo. Here, a classic piece of athleisurewear is given the label’s sleek, designer treatment, crafted in France from pure cotton loopback jersey and coated in jet black.

Digging into the archives to find these vintage prints, Saint Laurent bring back couture through throwback fashion moments. Dressed in black with breathable loopback as a base, this modern hoody bears YSL’s retro branding across the chest, sitting alongside the ‘damaged’ black and white imagery.

A fusion of collegiate and Parisian attire, this hoody takes cues from the 17th century Hôtel de Sénecterre that is now home to the Saint Laurent headquarters. Rich in yellow hues with a varsity-ready aesthetic, the 24 Rue de L’université print references HQ’s address, while the collegiate set-up of the design pays tribute to the house’s time in the USA.

In crisp, dazzling white, this pure cotton hoody from Saint Laurent cuts a sleek and simple athleisure shape. It is centrally branded with the label’s ‘60s revival logo and crafted in France for superior quality throughout. Engraved aglets and a tiny flash of red in the middle of the brand name remind of Saint Laurent’s eternally close attention to detail.

A new uniform for the Heron Preston fanatic, this season the designer steps into a new language, bringing Cantonese ‘style’ to this oversized hoody. Showcasing this global aesthetic with its ‘style’ branding in both Cyrillic and Cantonese, the US-born designer surrounds each print with a flock of abstract herons; delivering an iconic Preston look that’s set to take over the world.

Going on a world tour, Heron Preston delivers this sweatshirt with the label’s iconic ‘style’ print in both Cyrillic and Cantonese script. Preston says his phone background is always a satellite image of the world; which explains the global focus of the label, while circular heron prints sign off the relaxed-fitting silhouette with a dose of the designer’s graphic-heavy aesthetic.

The black cotton jersey hoodie – a classic athleisure staple – is given a high fashion update by Palm Angels. Shrunk to a cropped fit and finished with a wool mix embroidery of a beheaded teddy bear, it’s a comfy, cosy and super subversive final touch to put a streetwear spin on any outfit.

Crafted from Mako cotton jersey, this short sleeved tee is a garment dyed piece from Stone Island Shadow Project’s latest collection. Styled with a relaxed fit in mind, the t-shirt is stamped with signature graphics at its chest; while a rib knit collar leaves a comfortable finishing touch at its rounded neckline.

Putting an industrialised spin on Stone Island’s signature aesthetic, the brand’s Shadow Project line is crafted in association with techwear aficionado Errolson Hugh. Made from Mako jersey, this short-sleeved tee shows off a cool lavender colourway and its chest is stamped proudly with a seasonal ‘7019’ graphic.

A staple white tee that’s imbued with Stone Island Shadow Project’s signature graphic aesthetic, this Mako cotton tee is a short sleeved style from the esteemed Italian label. Trimmed with a ribbed collar, the t-shirt comes complete with a rib knit trim at its rounded crew neckline.

A relaxed blue tee from Stone Island Shadow Project, this ‘7019’ t-shirt is a Mako cotton style that’s built with both comfort and cool in mind. Stamped with printed branding at the front, the short sleeved style has been garment dyed and comes rounded out with a neat rib knit trim at its collar.

Existing under the casual-luxury umbrella of Stone Island, diffusion-line Stone Island Shadow Project return with the back print pocket tee. Visualised in a muted blue hue, this pure cotton deisgn honours the chest with a ‘7019’ print – a reference to its parent label and the new season ahead; featuring an asymmetric patch pocket, the nonchalant style is completed with a series of tiered graphics to its reverse, joined alongside the iconic compass logo.

Conceptualised to push the boundaries of menswear, Stone Island Shadow Project deliver the back print pocket tee, dressed here in lavender. Formulated with a '7019' print - a reference to Stone Island's core collection and the Shadow Project's season run, the pure cotton t-shirt is enhanced with an asymmetric pocket to its chest, joined dually to the front and reverse with dark printed branding.

Technical diffusion line Stone Island Shadow Project present this blacked-out t-shirt for your core rotation. Cut from the softest swatch of cotton, the premium tee arrives with reference to the sub-label’s parent brand and season run – depicted by the ‘7019’ graphic at the chest; complete with an asymmetric patch pocket, this casual style signs out with a graphic showcase to its reverse.

Rebellious to the core, Saint Laurent deliver this tee with a kaleidoscopic wild side. Housing colourful animal prints within the walls of its handwritten signature, the contemporary basic adds a luxurious touch to any off-duty look - prepped for the stylish streets of Paris with a soft jersey base that’s been crafted with care.

Like a polaroid picture, Saint Laurent look through an illustrated lens with this latest tee. Defined by its sketched-out glamourous graphic, the pops of colour and scripted branding deliver a truly Parisian state of mind. Wrapped in white with a soft jersey base, the Italian-made tee promises to bring a sense of luxury to your off-duty essentials.

A fashion statement in more ways than one, this Saint Laurent tee channels adverts of the past in a blocked black and white design. Lined with red and accented with the house’s ‘60s ‘Rive Gauche’ branding, the vintage tee comes straight from the Saint Laurent archives.

Kick back and relax this season in Stüssy’s Loungin’ tee, printed with autograph-like branding across the chest. Known for their legacy in surfing and skateboarding, the West Coast brands plays with new prints each season, riding their way into streetwear.

Taking a momentary break from skateboarding, Stüssy shows off their relaxed side with the Loungin’ tee. Detailed only with a small chest print, this otherwise plain white tee arrives just in time for summer.

Playing with Greek mythology this season, Stüssy uses Olympian god Zeus as inspiration for their grey heather tee. Known for their unique prints atop wardrobe staples, the skate and surf brand ventures into a new mythical realm.

Pigment-dyed to look like a thrift-store find, this black cotton tee from skate outfitter Stüssy is printed with a vintage-inspired logo at the rear for optimum retro appeal. The absinthe-green branding at the chest repeats across the back with an illustration of a 1940s painter daubing it on – a typically tongue-in-cheek touch from the original California streetwear brand.

Goddess of love in Roman mythology, Venus adorns the back of Stüssy’s tee, adding a mythical touch to your basic collection. Individually pigment dyed, each tee is unique and comes signed at the chest with the label’s iconic autograph-like branding.

Add a haunting touch to any outfit thanks to this spookily styled ‘Bats’ tee from Off-White. Made from cotton jersey, the black base layer is trimmed with a trusty ribbed collar; while an informative paragraph print at the back gives us an insight into the engineering of a bat’s wings.

Juxtaposing a dark skeletal scene with bold pops of pink, this Off-White tee is sure to turn heads as you venture into the new season. Made from cotton jersey with an oversized silhouette in mind, the cinematic style showcases bold ‘OFF’ branding at its chest and back.

Harnessing ‘thermo’ energy as it heads into the new season, Off-White delivers this vibrant oversized tee. Printed with techy graphics at its chest and back, the short sleeved style boasts a boxy build and its ribbed collar is completed in true Abloh style with a woven “A” tab.

Pushing the boundaries of modern streetwear, Cav Empt showcase their futuristic influences with the 'Not Liberate' tee. Sleekly dressed in black, the short sleeve style is given a hit of colour to the chest with a repeated purple graphic down the centre. Finished with the brand's signature typography to the reverse, wear by itself or pair with a shirt for a layered finish.

Distressed and then repaired for an authentic, worn in aesthetic, this ‘wharf’ wash iteration of John Elliott’s ‘The Cast 2’ jean is built from a Japanese denim that’s imbued with a subtle element of stretch. Equipped with a total of five functional pockets, these slim-fitting jeans are rounded out with a functional buttoned fly at the front.

Boasting a lived-in appearance, 'The Cast 2' jeans from John Elliott have been designed to last. Sure to become a wardrobe favourite, the Japanese-made essentials have been washed in a dark faded indigo, cut with a modern, slim fit for a street-ready look. Secured with a button fly, the denim pair are finished with a total of five functional pockets to the front and back.

Already boasting the look and feel of a love-worn favourite, these faded indigo ‘Cast 2’ jeans from John Elliott have been carefully crafted in Japan. Imbued with a subtle element of stretch, they have a whiskered appearance and are secured simply with a buttoned fly. Equipped with five pockets, this slim fitting pair are destined to be well worn for many seasons to come.

Cut from a stretch-infused Japanese denim, this carbon black iteration of John Elliott’s ‘Cast 2’ jean shows off a slim and tapered fit. Made in Japan with a low-rise that gradually gets higher towards the back, these jeans have a buttoned fly and come equipped with a total of five functional pockets; three at the front and two at the rear.

Crafted in Stone Island Shadow Project’s Italian homeland from an expert blend of cotton and linen, these ‘tie-up’ cargo pants show off both form and function. With an adjustable length, they are equipped with a total of six spacious pockets, while a handy zip fly secures their military-inspired look.

Embracing the utilitarian dimensions of the cargo pant, Italy’s Stone Island deliver this Italian-made pair in dark-navy. Technically constructed from a cotton-nylon blend, the garment dyed trousers strive to intensify the brand’s ‘Ghost’ concept with a tonal injection of the iconic compass patch at the thigh, blending into the monochromatic base, while a resin coated interior aims to provide heightened durability in the cold.

Saint Laurent luxury with a rugged sense of rock ‘n’ roll, this jean delivers premium flavour with a refined, slim fit. Crafted in Italy with a worn black denim, the casual set up lends itself to a well-worn aesthetic; channelling rebellious style with brass-tone hardware and a minimal design, while the quality denim construction speaks for itself.

Saint Laurent’s denim never fails to deliver, and this Japanese-made pair are perfect for adding rock ‘n’ roll appeal to the simplest of looks. Washed and faded with a greyscale look and feel, the sturdy denim silhouette brings a tapered slim fit; delivering a classic stance that’s heightened with Saint Laurent luxury.

A style you can rely upon time and time again, these regular tapered fit jeans from Italy’s Stone Island have been crafted using 13oz selvedge denim which has been meticulously sourced from the fabric’s adopted capital in Japan. Residing mid-rise on the waist, this luxury pair feature the brand’s iconic compass patch on the reverse, affiliated alongside a five-pocket set up, presenting convenient space for your keys, wallet and phone alike.

Maison Margiela’s Classic Replica sneaker is as sleek as they come. Rendered here in sophisticated tan calfskin with suede accents and an old school gum rubber outsole, they are simply designed with luxe detailing throughout. As a perfect finishing touch, a suede brand patch at the tongue offers a subtle hint of designer charm.

The sleek silhouette of these low-rise grey sneakers from Maison Margiela allows the shoe’s multiple textures to be expertly explored. Soft calfskin uppers are accented with corresponding grey suede, while tonal grey rubber outsoles and laces complete the look. A grey suede brand patch at the tongue rounds things off perfectly.

These retro-inspired low rise leather sneakers from Maison Margiela are a simple, sophisticated shoe with street appeal in spades. Crafted from soft blue calfskin, the uppers are decorated with suede accents and sit comfortably in an old school gum rubber outsole. A suede brand patch at the tongue and contrasting toile-coloured twill laces complete the combination of textures perfectly.

An update on one of Maison Margiela’s trademark luxury sneakers, this pair of painter ‘Replica’ sneakers come dressed with all-black suede uppers and gummy rubber outsoles. Complete with the brand’s signature paint drop finish, this lamb and calfskin shoe is constructed to deliver both comfort and supreme style with every step. Finished with the brand’s iconic numerical logo debossed to the tongue, a subtle singular stitch sits proudly at the heel.

Well known for their skilful reinterpretations of classic sneaker styles, Maison Margiela breathe new life into their storied ‘Replica’ silhouette this season. Built with smooth leather uppers that have then been overlaid with a touch of suede, this black and amber pair are completed with single stitch detailing at the heels.

Clean-cut and streamlined, Nike update the Air Max 1 with a sporty ‘Light Bone’ colourway. Blocking off jet black with warm beige accents, this iteration of the contemporary Air Max icon is dressed for the streets. Underfoot Max Air cushioning reacts for peak performance – bringing premium comfort to the sneaker’s gum rubber sole.

Take to the skies in style thanks to this all-white pair of Nike Air Force 1 '07’s. A style that recalls a classic hoops profile, this pair are punctuated with premium detailing and come sat atop this brands iconic Air-Sole cushioning.

Dressed in rich green tones, Nike deliver their storied Air Max 1 silhouette with mesh, suede and leather uppers this season. Signed off with Swoosh branding at the side wall, this Max Air cushioned pair have comfortable foam midsoles, whilst robust rubber outsoles add a durable finishing touch at the base.

From court to couture, Saint Laurent deliver luxury with an effortlessly cool touch. Bringing the SL-06 into the spotlight in a rough and ready rendition, the Parisian house dress this pair with a distressed look and feel. Cotton canvas lines the uppers; overlaid with textured suede accents, while a scripted Saint Laurent signature is embroidered across the sidewalls.

A luxury hi-top to add to your Saint Laurent wardrobe, this Joe sneaker steps up to the street in the softest calfskin leathers. Purposely distressed for a worn-in look and feel, the vintage white and cherry red design harks back to Saint Laurent’s YSL branding; imprinting the iconic logo underfoot for a subtle finishing touch.

The perfect balance of sleek and sporty, the Saint Laurent's SL-06's canvas uppers have been distressed and branded with the label's irrefutably grunge-cool aesthetic. Made to the highest possible standard in Italy, the sneaker takes on the traditional styling of an on-court classic and elevates it to luxurious new heights.

A fusion of collegiate and Parisian attire, this hoody takes cues from the 17th century Hôtel de Sénecterre that is now home to the Saint Laurent headquarters. Rich in yellow hues with a varsity-ready aesthetic, the 24 Rue de L’université print references HQ’s address, while the collegiate set-up of the design pays tribute to the house’s time in the USA.

In crisp, dazzling white, this pure cotton hoody from Saint Laurent cuts a sleek and simple athleisure shape. It is centrally branded with the label’s ‘60s revival logo and crafted in France for superior quality throughout. Engraved aglets and a tiny flash of red in the middle of the brand name remind of Saint Laurent’s eternally close attention to detail.

A new uniform for the Heron Preston fanatic, this season the designer steps into a new language, bringing Cantonese ‘style’ to this oversized hoody. Showcasing this global aesthetic with its ‘style’ branding in both Cyrillic and Cantonese, the US-born designer surrounds each print with a flock of abstract herons; delivering an iconic Preston look that’s set to take over the world.

Going on a world tour, Heron Preston delivers this sweatshirt with the label’s iconic ‘style’ print in both Cyrillic and Cantonese script. Preston says his phone background is always a satellite image of the world; which explains the global focus of the label, while circular heron prints sign off the relaxed-fitting silhouette with a dose of the designer’s graphic-heavy aesthetic.

The black cotton jersey hoodie – a classic athleisure staple – is given a high fashion update by Palm Angels. Shrunk to a cropped fit and finished with a wool mix embroidery of a beheaded teddy bear, it’s a comfy, cosy and super subversive final touch to put a streetwear spin on any outfit.

Crafted from Mako cotton jersey, this short sleeved tee is a garment dyed piece from Stone Island Shadow Project’s latest collection. Styled with a relaxed fit in mind, the t-shirt is stamped with signature graphics at its chest; while a rib knit collar leaves a comfortable finishing touch at its rounded neckline.

Putting an industrialised spin on Stone Island’s signature aesthetic, the brand’s Shadow Project line is crafted in association with techwear aficionado Errolson Hugh. Made from Mako jersey, this short-sleeved tee shows off a cool lavender colourway and its chest is stamped proudly with a seasonal ‘7019’ graphic.

A staple white tee that’s imbued with Stone Island Shadow Project’s signature graphic aesthetic, this Mako cotton tee is a short sleeved style from the esteemed Italian label. Trimmed with a ribbed collar, the t-shirt comes complete with a rib knit trim at its rounded crew neckline.

A relaxed blue tee from Stone Island Shadow Project, this ‘7019’ t-shirt is a Mako cotton style that’s built with both comfort and cool in mind. Stamped with printed branding at the front, the short sleeved style has been garment dyed and comes rounded out with a neat rib knit trim at its collar.

Existing under the casual-luxury umbrella of Stone Island, diffusion-line Stone Island Shadow Project return with the back print pocket tee. Visualised in a muted blue hue, this pure cotton deisgn honours the chest with a ‘7019’ print – a reference to its parent label and the new season ahead; featuring an asymmetric patch pocket, the nonchalant style is completed with a series of tiered graphics to its reverse, joined alongside the iconic compass logo.

Conceptualised to push the boundaries of menswear, Stone Island Shadow Project deliver the back print pocket tee, dressed here in lavender. Formulated with a '7019' print - a reference to Stone Island's core collection and the Shadow Project's season run, the pure cotton t-shirt is enhanced with an asymmetric pocket to its chest, joined dually to the front and reverse with dark printed branding.

Technical diffusion line Stone Island Shadow Project present this blacked-out t-shirt for your core rotation. Cut from the softest swatch of cotton, the premium tee arrives with reference to the sub-label’s parent brand and season run – depicted by the ‘7019’ graphic at the chest; complete with an asymmetric patch pocket, this casual style signs out with a graphic showcase to its reverse.

Rebellious to the core, Saint Laurent deliver this tee with a kaleidoscopic wild side. Housing colourful animal prints within the walls of its handwritten signature, the contemporary basic adds a luxurious touch to any off-duty look - prepped for the stylish streets of Paris with a soft jersey base that’s been crafted with care.

Like a polaroid picture, Saint Laurent look through an illustrated lens with this latest tee. Defined by its sketched-out glamourous graphic, the pops of colour and scripted branding deliver a truly Parisian state of mind. Wrapped in white with a soft jersey base, the Italian-made tee promises to bring a sense of luxury to your off-duty essentials.

A fashion statement in more ways than one, this Saint Laurent tee channels adverts of the past in a blocked black and white design. Lined with red and accented with the house’s ‘60s ‘Rive Gauche’ branding, the vintage tee comes straight from the Saint Laurent archives.

Kick back and relax this season in Stüssy’s Loungin’ tee, printed with autograph-like branding across the chest. Known for their legacy in surfing and skateboarding, the West Coast brands plays with new prints each season, riding their way into streetwear.

Taking a momentary break from skateboarding, Stüssy shows off their relaxed side with the Loungin’ tee. Detailed only with a small chest print, this otherwise plain white tee arrives just in time for summer.

Playing with Greek mythology this season, Stüssy uses Olympian god Zeus as inspiration for their grey heather tee. Known for their unique prints atop wardrobe staples, the skate and surf brand ventures into a new mythical realm.

Pigment-dyed to look like a thrift-store find, this black cotton tee from skate outfitter Stüssy is printed with a vintage-inspired logo at the rear for optimum retro appeal. The absinthe-green branding at the chest repeats across the back with an illustration of a 1940s painter daubing it on – a typically tongue-in-cheek touch from the original California streetwear brand.

Goddess of love in Roman mythology, Venus adorns the back of Stüssy’s tee, adding a mythical touch to your basic collection. Individually pigment dyed, each tee is unique and comes signed at the chest with the label’s iconic autograph-like branding.

Add a haunting touch to any outfit thanks to this spookily styled ‘Bats’ tee from Off-White. Made from cotton jersey, the black base layer is trimmed with a trusty ribbed collar; while an informative paragraph print at the back gives us an insight into the engineering of a bat’s wings.

Juxtaposing a dark skeletal scene with bold pops of pink, this Off-White tee is sure to turn heads as you venture into the new season. Made from cotton jersey with an oversized silhouette in mind, the cinematic style showcases bold ‘OFF’ branding at its chest and back.

Harnessing ‘thermo’ energy as it heads into the new season, Off-White delivers this vibrant oversized tee. Printed with techy graphics at its chest and back, the short sleeved style boasts a boxy build and its ribbed collar is completed in true Abloh style with a woven “A” tab.

Pushing the boundaries of modern streetwear, Cav Empt showcase their futuristic influences with the 'Not Liberate' tee. Sleekly dressed in black, the short sleeve style is given a hit of colour to the chest with a repeated purple graphic down the centre. Finished with the brand's signature typography to the reverse, wear by itself or pair with a shirt for a layered finish.

Distressed and then repaired for an authentic, worn in aesthetic, this ‘wharf’ wash iteration of John Elliott’s ‘The Cast 2’ jean is built from a Japanese denim that’s imbued with a subtle element of stretch. Equipped with a total of five functional pockets, these slim-fitting jeans are rounded out with a functional buttoned fly at the front.

Boasting a lived-in appearance, 'The Cast 2' jeans from John Elliott have been designed to last. Sure to become a wardrobe favourite, the Japanese-made essentials have been washed in a dark faded indigo, cut with a modern, slim fit for a street-ready look. Secured with a button fly, the denim pair are finished with a total of five functional pockets to the front and back.

Already boasting the look and feel of a love-worn favourite, these faded indigo ‘Cast 2’ jeans from John Elliott have been carefully crafted in Japan. Imbued with a subtle element of stretch, they have a whiskered appearance and are secured simply with a buttoned fly. Equipped with five pockets, this slim fitting pair are destined to be well worn for many seasons to come.

Cut from a stretch-infused Japanese denim, this carbon black iteration of John Elliott’s ‘Cast 2’ jean shows off a slim and tapered fit. Made in Japan with a low-rise that gradually gets higher towards the back, these jeans have a buttoned fly and come equipped with a total of five functional pockets; three at the front and two at the rear.

Crafted in Stone Island Shadow Project’s Italian homeland from an expert blend of cotton and linen, these ‘tie-up’ cargo pants show off both form and function. With an adjustable length, they are equipped with a total of six spacious pockets, while a handy zip fly secures their military-inspired look.

Embracing the utilitarian dimensions of the cargo pant, Italy’s Stone Island deliver this Italian-made pair in dark-navy. Technically constructed from a cotton-nylon blend, the garment dyed trousers strive to intensify the brand’s ‘Ghost’ concept with a tonal injection of the iconic compass patch at the thigh, blending into the monochromatic base, while a resin coated interior aims to provide heightened durability in the cold.

Saint Laurent luxury with a rugged sense of rock ‘n’ roll, this jean delivers premium flavour with a refined, slim fit. Crafted in Italy with a worn black denim, the casual set up lends itself to a well-worn aesthetic; channelling rebellious style with brass-tone hardware and a minimal design, while the quality denim construction speaks for itself.

Saint Laurent’s denim never fails to deliver, and this Japanese-made pair are perfect for adding rock ‘n’ roll appeal to the simplest of looks. Washed and faded with a greyscale look and feel, the sturdy denim silhouette brings a tapered slim fit; delivering a classic stance that’s heightened with Saint Laurent luxury.

A style you can rely upon time and time again, these regular tapered fit jeans from Italy’s Stone Island have been crafted using 13oz selvedge denim which has been meticulously sourced from the fabric’s adopted capital in Japan. Residing mid-rise on the waist, this luxury pair feature the brand’s iconic compass patch on the reverse, affiliated alongside a five-pocket set up, presenting convenient space for your keys, wallet and phone alike.

Maison Margiela’s Classic Replica sneaker is as sleek as they come. Rendered here in sophisticated tan calfskin with suede accents and an old school gum rubber outsole, they are simply designed with luxe detailing throughout. As a perfect finishing touch, a suede brand patch at the tongue offers a subtle hint of designer charm.

The sleek silhouette of these low-rise grey sneakers from Maison Margiela allows the shoe’s multiple textures to be expertly explored. Soft calfskin uppers are accented with corresponding grey suede, while tonal grey rubber outsoles and laces complete the look. A grey suede brand patch at the tongue rounds things off perfectly.

These retro-inspired low rise leather sneakers from Maison Margiela are a simple, sophisticated shoe with street appeal in spades. Crafted from soft blue calfskin, the uppers are decorated with suede accents and sit comfortably in an old school gum rubber outsole. A suede brand patch at the tongue and contrasting toile-coloured twill laces complete the combination of textures perfectly.

An update on one of Maison Margiela’s trademark luxury sneakers, this pair of painter ‘Replica’ sneakers come dressed with all-black suede uppers and gummy rubber outsoles. Complete with the brand’s signature paint drop finish, this lamb and calfskin shoe is constructed to deliver both comfort and supreme style with every step. Finished with the brand’s iconic numerical logo debossed to the tongue, a subtle singular stitch sits proudly at the heel.

Well known for their skilful reinterpretations of classic sneaker styles, Maison Margiela breathe new life into their storied ‘Replica’ silhouette this season. Built with smooth leather uppers that have then been overlaid with a touch of suede, this black and amber pair are completed with single stitch detailing at the heels.

Clean-cut and streamlined, Nike update the Air Max 1 with a sporty ‘Light Bone’ colourway. Blocking off jet black with warm beige accents, this iteration of the contemporary Air Max icon is dressed for the streets. Underfoot Max Air cushioning reacts for peak performance – bringing premium comfort to the sneaker’s gum rubber sole.

Take to the skies in style thanks to this all-white pair of Nike Air Force 1 '07’s. A style that recalls a classic hoops profile, this pair are punctuated with premium detailing and come sat atop this brands iconic Air-Sole cushioning.

Dressed in rich green tones, Nike deliver their storied Air Max 1 silhouette with mesh, suede and leather uppers this season. Signed off with Swoosh branding at the side wall, this Max Air cushioned pair have comfortable foam midsoles, whilst robust rubber outsoles add a durable finishing touch at the base.

From court to couture, Saint Laurent deliver luxury with an effortlessly cool touch. Bringing the SL-06 into the spotlight in a rough and ready rendition, the Parisian house dress this pair with a distressed look and feel. Cotton canvas lines the uppers; overlaid with textured suede accents, while a scripted Saint Laurent signature is embroidered across the sidewalls.

A luxury hi-top to add to your Saint Laurent wardrobe, this Joe sneaker steps up to the street in the softest calfskin leathers. Purposely distressed for a worn-in look and feel, the vintage white and cherry red design harks back to Saint Laurent’s YSL branding; imprinting the iconic logo underfoot for a subtle finishing touch.

The perfect balance of sleek and sporty, the Saint Laurent's SL-06's canvas uppers have been distressed and branded with the label's irrefutably grunge-cool aesthetic. Made to the highest possible standard in Italy, the sneaker takes on the traditional styling of an on-court classic and elevates it to luxurious new heights.
